{"type":"message","id":"05e7e0ec","parentId":"6e53cf10","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:43:59.058Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering polling strategy**\n\nI’m thinking I need to avoid rapid polling loops to make everything run smoothly. It seems that polling once with a timeout of maybe 30 seconds could be a better approach. It gives enough time before checking again, which should help with efficiency and avoid overwhelming the system. I wonder if this is the best timeout or if a little more time might be helpful too. It’s all about finding that sweet spot!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_00990316fdaeab850169cf0d4c35cc8198ab8bf46cb3dea587\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpzw1OnUMIqz56mZj8vpVj4ywUHn7rqhMDvKByRtk2g4hXRO1e5gGJ49LqOLHwtspLNiavhqpN0u3h3-4rdi4VM12hsM4ZnvZwmLeVYOwJuQXVwP044tJVsJgy_upEtKJPTQ3_kUbKmbkMWDHMgpMSluK8tPtcChbzbltUgENfkk__Ed0OzYIwpGTK6G8fUJtb3aL8GPr8tgQWq3YxkEVN0zAFvh3IOwl4G-MH9hYd7995ATEsJxU-o0JZCRImtGRT0wRJV7pdyclAw5oMX9uGyI5ouzQYKIbOz_7ZPKLEOWD8zcq2plecIV4vLtTlEcdgMTy44-yCLWsdF98SWgX707jnFqjdsj4aXymRyFxvuM0GD-DD4XXzuYPaGyfybV5xYYHqc-z9ntgyEncqVMikUwQQmKT4gtnDbeQPVE7TEz6sXhzhhPOGML_JlL8rscy1Z08Jg342_2_mUdggFR0_ZticR96yhGVU6Y81NrSg8W3rLuh-tNIos3RF9dji6bdSO6e4f8cpMQxu5NqzSt4r8_7NnpFdJfwpSEsylBWIOzBlSLWP4-h9Z3icE2LZTggK78sLmK4NfZwg7qkovTG_z5k_8uMwDcNajZTZ2mjnY-kmO5i45MAGdVQlBAFIegvAdMPdw-TZyV6FNP6MxHhspCb21xt84UeLwZveOdg4Wxz-9uqHmWmTsPalNC6wD99CnvjyR0zf4PB635wjwgDPJnziQ_YIllo-iG466_rAWSQvrk0EwzzMbIjdcX38tqO_12Zs-fv2jKftFozzMPV-amws4BWJIrg_pZJeQGKOjNFNultFlkp5tZ4Qt5iAW1uX59oxc6xOxeZldtDRJ6qR9DcCljmBRXyypIJ7070anuL5NkiMxhabwYlHI5C5xabtfPqCJ6BXyDYwYyT6-_dqMQnaRw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering polling strategy**\\n\\nI’m thinking I need to avoid rapid polling loops to make everything run smoothly. It seems that polling once with a timeout of maybe 30 seconds could be a better approach. It gives enough time before checking again, which should 