:\"**Resolving review date issue**\\n\\nI'm seeing a problem: the manual review isn't found because the runtime date tag has updated to 20260403, but our expected review JSON runtime date tag is 20260402. I need to integrate despite this newer tag. Should I use drawdown review context or the expected trade date? Hmm, it seems like we could load the latest review JSON instead of requiring an exact match. I'd suggest fixing the helper function to fall back on the latest review JSON if the exact one isn’t found.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Adjusting report handling**\\n\\nI can modify the helper function to first look for the exact runtime date tag, and if that isn't found, use the latest file. The current report path is set to an exact date tag of 20260402, which means it's relying on an outdated gate without a manual review since that specific report wasn’t regenerated. I could either rerun the gate to create the latest report or make it so the system prefers the latest if it’s more recent. I need to think about which option works best for the user.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering governance gate generation**\\n\\nI’m wondering if I can adjust the script to generate a governance gate for 20260402. However, since today is 20260403, the report is anticipating a trade date of 20260402. The governance gate status function selects the exact file that matches the date tag, so it specifically looks for 20260402. Maybe I need to rethink how this process works in order to ensure I’m getting the right files for current operations.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"根因找到了：`today report` 还在优先读旧的 `20260402` gate 文件，而我刚把建议层接进的是更新后的 latest。现在补一个回退逻辑，老 dated 文件也能拿到最新建议层。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00990316fdaeab850169cf1cef7638819885250592e1511d5d\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_LqHJzCdhDApFsZ5sd4J0q1hd|fc_00990316fdaeab850169cf1ceffd808198aa4937527c6f4d3d","name":"edit","arguments":{"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_governance_gate.py","oldText":"def load_drawdown_manual_review(runtime_date_tag: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    normalized = str(runtime_date_tag or \"\").strip()\n    if not normalized:\n        return {}\n    for path in sorted(REPORT_DIR.glob(DRAWDOWN_REVIEW_REPORT_GLOB), reverse=True):\n        payload = load_json(path)\n        if str(payload.get(\"runtime_date_tag\") or \"\").strip() == normalized:\n            payload[\"_path\"] = str(path)\n            return payload\n    return {}\n","newText":"def load_drawdown_manual_review(runtime_date_tag: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    normalized = str(runtime_date_tag or \"\").strip()\n    latest_payload: dict[str, Any] = {}\n    for path in sorted(REPORT_DIR.glob(DRAWDOWN_REVIEW_REPORT_GLOB), reverse=True):\n        payload = load_json(path)\n        if payload and not latest_payload:\n            payload[\"_path\"] = str(path)\n            latest_payload = payload\n        if normalized and str(payload.get(\"runtime_date_tag\") or \"\").strip() == normalized:\n            payload[\"_path\"] = str(path)\n            return payload\n    return latest_payload\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_governance_gate.py\",\"oldText\":\"def load_drawdown_manual_review(runtime_date_tag: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    normalized = str(runtime_date_tag or \\\"\\\").strip()\\n    if not normalized:\\n        return {}\\n    for path in sorted(REPORT_DIR.glob(DRAWDOWN_REVIEW_REPORT_GLOB), reverse=True):\\n        payload = load_json(path)\\n        if str(payload.get(\\\"runtime_date_tag\\\") or \\\"\\\").strip() == normalized:\\n            payload[\\\"_path\\\"] = str(path)\\n            return payload\\n    return {}\\n\",\"newText\":\"def load_drawdown_manual_review(runtime_date_tag: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    normalized = str(runtime_date_tag or \\\"\\\").strip()\\n    latest_payload: dict[str, Any] = {}\\n    for path in sorted(REPORT_DIR.glob(DRAWDOWN_REVIEW_REPORT_GLOB), reverse=True):\\n        payload = load_json(path)\\n        if payload and not latest_payload:\\n            payload[\\\"_path\\\"] = str(path)\\n            latest_payload = payload\\n        if normalized and str(payload.get(\\\"runtime_date_tag\\\") or \\\"\\\").strip() == normalized:\\n            payload[\\\"_path\\\"] = str(path)\\n            return payload\\n    return latest_payload\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":134192,"output":1682,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135874,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775180972396,"responseId":"resp_00990316fdaeab850169cf1ccf0e948198b28fba1ce124f5ad"}}
