{"type":"message","id":"88429cbe","parentId":"ab16d868","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:25:14.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The conservative shadow has been re-run with the unified runtime truth. The results are consistent with before:\n- conservative vs baseline: ann_ret +17.24pp, max_dd -1.38pp, sharpe +0.23\n\nNow let me analyze what this means and update the ACTIVE_TASK. The key point is that:\n1. The conservative shadow is still showing better metrics than baseline\n2. But the previous issue (True -> False change) is now in the past - the current market is still risk_off/halt\n3. The BLOCK from governance is still in place\n\nSo the situation is:\n- Conservative shadow: still shows better metrics\n\n\n- Governance BLOCK: still active (need sign-off)\n- Market status: still FULL_HALT (risk_off=true, halt_new_buy=true)\n\nThe conservative shadow is generating fresh results for 20260403 that align with our unified runtime truth, which validates our earlier observations. However, the decision brief's original reasoning about the True -> False change was actually pointing to a data inconsistency between the shadow and live markets at that time. Now with unified metrics, this particular concern has been resolved, though we're left with the question of what the correct trading stance should actually be given the market remains halted.\n\nThe BLOCK remains in place because the governance sign-off is still needed, so there's nothing actionable here. I'll commit these new results and update the task with the conservative shadow outcomes for 20260403.","thinkingSignature":"c6e0645ce017563661029656b9dc712a363414403a5583f7cbd8bbd720e19176"},{"type":"text","text":"conservative shadow 重跑完成。指标跟之前一致：新数据用统一口径重新验证了方向，但市场仍是 FULL_HALT，BLOCK 未解除。更新任务状态并提交。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mmd45pplzzqv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && git status --short \\\nquant_projects/personal-a-sha