{"type":"message","id":"1de68088","parentId":"bb8fba1a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:28:40.492Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to proceed with \"补签字\" - signing the governance review document. This means I need to update the `strategy_drawdown_governance_review_20260403.json` with actual signature dates and potentially update the `strategy_registry_v2.json` with the decisions.\n\nLet me think about what \"补签字\" means in this context:\n1. Take the `strategy_drawdown_governance_review_signoff_20260403.md` and fill in the signature fields (research_owner, risk_owner, decision_date)\n2. Update the JSON file with actual signoff values\n3. Potentially update the strategy registry with the conclusions\n\n\n4. Since Zhang Ling has implicitly authorized this by requesting it, I'll proceed with adding the signature date (2026-04-03) and updating the JSON with the signed values, then update the strategy registry accordingly.\n\nFor the registry updates, I need to downgrade `smallcap_chip_v4_2_alpha_recover` from \"current main candidate\" to \"watch candidate\" status, mark `rd_agent_top2_gray_v1` as retired, and note that `smallcap_chip_v4_1_alpha_guard` remains unchanged.\n\nI'll need to modify the registry JSON files to reflect these state changes, update the governance gate, and then re-run the scripts to propagate these updates through the system. Let me start by examining the registry structure to understand how to properly implement these changes.","thinkingSignature":"d6a3f6e700d34e045fbb656e9093da6a782350bbd1a294b6306dd8734890aea8"},{"type":"text","text":"收到。我直接把签字结论写进 JSON 和 registry，让系统链路能读到签字完成状态。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3qtwk9tqyysp_1","name":"write","arguments":{"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md","content":"Status: active\nPriority: P1\nStarted: 2026-04-03 10:29\nUpdated: 2026-04-03 10:29\nWorkspace: /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-s